sd=Business Development	Define, implement, track and assess the new business development plans	Corporate strategy develops targets for new business acquisition in selected market segments	Define, implement, track and assess the new business development plans for the enterprise or specific business divisions. This can cover business activities such as new market segment entry, product coverage and product specification development, brand development, new customer acquisition and existing customer, cross-sell/up-sell and retention.
sdpath=business-development
crpath=business-development-strategy
crr=Business Development Strategy Instance
mcr=Business Development Strategy
bqs=Initiative
